.TH LPF-MAN 8 "June 2026" "lpf 0.2.3" "lpf Manual"
.SH NAME
lpf\-man \- generate, check, or install man pages
.SH SYNOPSIS
lpf man <generate|check|install>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Generate, check, or install man pages from OCaml command metadata.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\-\-dir <path>
select generated man page directory for generate/check
.TP
\-\-prefix <path>
install pages under the prefix share/man tree
.SH EXAMPLES
lpf man generate
lpf man check
lpf man install \-\-prefix /usr/local
.SH FILES
man/generated
/usr/local/share/man
.SH SAFETY NOTES
Generated man pages must be committed with command behavior changes.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success.
Non\-zero when validation, planning, or host operations fail.
.SH SEE ALSO
lpf(8), lpf.conf(5)
